column5: Good time had by all !!! We had a great time in London this evening...Lots of fishing filtered try again please chat and a few new faces as well....  Looking forward to seeing you all agian soon... Cheers !!
Ur home allready?.....lol  Glad you all had a great time.
it is 11.02pm on a saterday night....Behave urslef.......lol
LOL!! I was the last one to leave and that was  8:30... I had to bribe Chris and Brian to hang out a little longer!!
A good turnout.  Wish I was closer. I may have passed by to say hello.....in person. Glad to hear it was a good time for our southwestern Ontario members.
blimey 8.30pm?  And i thought i left the oakville swill early at allmost midnight.....lol and i had over an hrs drive back to PD.....lol  Man u old lot of  *(*&      LOL...Okay just teasing.....

Nauti, Ya,we definetely packed in a little early tonight....I think there was a hockey game or somethin ???? Ended up over at Fishnchips for one last cold one before headin home...... Oh,and thanx again Slowpoke for keepin us around for that last cold one

By 8PM we figured you weren't coming so everybody finished thier non-alchoholic beverages and headed home for a good nights sleep to be fresh for early mass in the morning. Okay, just kidding... The truth is we kept getting hit-on by a group of ravishing young ladies with facial hair fetishes... it was horrible. Riddled with guilt, we chose to call it an early evening and return home to our awaiting spouses. -Brian
OHH GAWD I HEARD IT ALL NOW...... :   FACIAL HAIR FETISHES HUH....LOL........
Looks like a great time guys.  We had one up at our end also.  Joey
Looks like a good time guys next time old man winter might not show here and I will take the drive down

Was a great time meeting old and new faces again, Thanks for coming,good food ,great convos,cold beer, hopefully next time the weather will cooperate. I heard on the news there were close to 500 accidents around TO.We will have to figure out when to plan the next one,maybe Feb or Mar,I won't even discuss Gary showing up in that Bears shirt lol  Brian
another g2g last night.it was good to see everyone out.by the way what kind of burger was that.hehe
huge, apparently everyone left early after eating them to go home and have a nap lol looked like a pound of meat on them,they looked good though Brian
Looked like a great time everyone!  Nice pics...and sorry to hear about those young women with facial hair fetishes....they spoil it every time....haha.
looks like everyone had a great time,lots of happy faces and conversation...glad to see lots of people came out   cheers everyone

It was great once again to see some old faces and meet some new people.  Conversation was non stop and all seemed to enjoy themselves.  Bad weather held off so everyone could have a safe trip home.  I'm sure that if the weather would not have been so "iffy"  we would have stayed longer.  It was super to hear that Fish and Chips will have an easier time this year at Silvr'y Moon I.E. more time for fishing!!!!  And by the way those burgers are called " Brontausaurus  Burgers"  12oz of burger with cheese, grilled and raw onions, pickles, tomato and lettuce fries with gravy.   I had one last time and another yesterday, next G2G I'll have another!

they did look pretty good Gary,and yes with 3 extra days fishing and no travelling to Sudbury it will be more like a vacation,especially for my wife and daughter who had to try and stay busy for 4 hours at the Mall ,good to see you and glad you made it back home ok, Brian
